MUTUA MADRID OPEN
May 2, 2014
Serena Williams
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









  THE MODERATOR:   Questions, please. 

Q.   Tell us about your first impressions here in Madrid?
SERENA WILLIAMS:   You guys know I love Madrid.   I love coming here.   It's the reason why I come back every year.   I mostly love the city.   It's just so pretty. 
The food, it love obviously, so it's great.
Any other takers?

Q.   You have a very good record in Madrid over the last couple years.   What makes it special for you on the clay here compared to other tournaments?
SERENA WILLIAMS:   I don't know.   I love playing here.   I hate leaving, I guess.   I don't want to leave.   I want to kind of stay.
So I just really enjoy my time here.   I love Madrid.   I love the tournament directors and the people that run it.   They just do a really good job to try to make everyone happy. 

Q.   Your feelings and sensations now?
SERENA WILLIAMS:   I feel good.   I feel really good.   I feel positive, and I think that's what matters most. 

Q.   After Charleston you said you needed some time off tennis.   How are you mentally right now?
SERENA WILLIAMS:   I'm so much better.   I took so much time off.   I needed it.   I had just been playing for such a long time nonstop.   It was actually really good for me to get that off.
I'm good now. 







END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT